@node control_panel "Control Panel"

                              @{b}2.1 Control Panel
                             ===================@{ub}

With this window you can control the complete program. The Help-key shows you
the  online  help.  The  escape-key  is  used to close (cancel) a window, the
return  key  is used to confirm a window (ok). If you want to save the window
position on a publicscreen, you just have to save the preferences.

If you want to abort a running game, click on the Game-Menu-gadget.

Gadgets for program control:

@{" Quit        " link quit}   Quit the program
@{" Recalculate " link recalculate}   Calculate a new landscape
@{" Game Menu   " link game_menu}   Game Menu Window
@{" Player Menu " link player_menu}   Player Menu Window
@{" Preferences " link preferences}   Preferences Window
@{" Highscore   " link highscore}   Highscore Window
@{" Network     " link network}   Network Window
@{" About       " link about}   About Window

Gadgets for cannon control:

@{" Weapon      " link weapon}   Change the weapon
@{" Barrel      " link barrel}   Change the angle
@{" Powder      " link powder}   Change the amount of powder used
@{" Move        " link move}   Change the cannon position

Information gadgets:

@{" Victories   " link victories}   Number of victories
@{" Damage      " link damage}   How much damage have you suffered?

The  colored display (green -> yellow -> red) shows the damage of the weapon,
the blue display shows the energy stock.


You can control the cannons with the keyboard (numeric block) too:

Weapon: keys - and +
Barrel: keys 7 and 9
Powder: keys 4 and 6
Move:   keys 1 and 3
Fire:   Enter


In addition you can control the cannons with a gamepad:

Weapon: green and yellow keys
Barrel: joystick up and down
Powder: joystick left and right
Move:   forward and reverse keys
Fire:   red key


With the blue button (resp. shift key) you can activate the "fast mode", i.e.
if  you  hold  down  the  blue button and change the angle of the barrel, the
angle will change quicker.

@endnode


@node quit "Quit the program"

With this gadget you can quit the program.

@endnode


@node recalculate "Recalculate"

With this gadget you can calculate a new landscape. It is activated only if a
new  duel is started and no player has fired yet. So you have the possibility
to change an "unfair" landscape.

@endnode


@node weapon "Change the weapon"

The  window  with  the weapon selection is opened with the right mousebutton!
Now  you  can  change  the  actual weapon (click with left mousebutton on the
appropriate  gadget)  or  close  the window with the right mousebutton. Right
beside the weapon the amount of energie the weapon uses is shown.

Every cannon has an energie stock of 100 points. For every used weapon points
are  taken  off  this  stock,  until  the  amount  of energy isn't sufficient
anymore.  Then  the  only possible weapon is "Air Raid". All damages that are
repaired  automatically  (barrel,  powder,  move  and anemometer) require one
energy point, too.


There are five different weapons:

· Normal Shot:

  This is the normal cannonball.

· Parachute:

  This cannonball has a parachute, which opens if the cannonball falls down.
  Because of the parachute, it is very wind sensitive.

· Energy Flash:

  With this weapon one can reduce the energy stock of the opponent. It works,
  if one hits the basis, too, but only with a reduced effect.

· Rocket:

  This is a rocket, which automatically aims for the opponents cannon.

· Air Raid:

  After a radio message is sent, a bomber flies into the screen.  The bomb is
  dropped after a click on the "FIRE" gadget.  The special on this weapon is,
  that it uses two rounds (1. round: radio message,  2. round: bomber flies).
  This weapon uses no energy.  Because of  this,  it is the only weapon which
  is useable after the energy stock is used up.

The cannon can be repaired with "Repair".

This table shows all weapons, the appropriate costs and the caused damages:

                                Damage (Cannon)    Damage (Basis)
        Weapon       | Costs  |    Min |    Max |    Min |    Max |
        -----------------------------------------------------------
        Normal Shot  |      5 |      1 |     50 |      - |      - |
        Parachute    |     10 |     40 |    100 |      - |      - |
        Energy Flash |     20 |     30 |     50 |      5 |     10 |
        Rocket       |     40 |     25 |    100 |      - |      - |
        Bomber       |      0 |     25 |    100 |      - |      - |
        Repair       |     40 |     20 |     50 |      - |      - |

The 'damage' of an "Energy Flash" corresponds to the amount of energy that is
subtracted   of   the  opponents  energy  stock,  the  'damage'  of  "Repair"
corresponds to the amount of damages that are repaired (in procent).

@endnode


@node barrel "Barrel"

With  this  slider gadget you can change the angle of the barrel. The allowed
range is 0 to 90°.

@endnode


@node powder "Powder"

With  this  slider  gadget  you  can change the amount of powder. The allowed
range is 1 to 200 (1 means 'very feeble', 200 means 'very strong').

@endnode


@node move "Move"

With this slider gadget you can change the position of the cannon.

@endnode


@node victories "Victories"

In this gadget the number of victories of the actual game are displayed.

@endnode


@node damage "Damage"

In this gadget the damage status of the cannon is shown (0 means 'no damage',
100  means  'write-off').  Furthermore  you can see the damage on the colored
display.

The  cannon  can  be  damaged  in four ways. These are displayed right to the
corresponding gadget. Green means all is working well, yellow means there are
light damages and red means there are heavy damages. If the windgauge is hit,
the  wind  for  the next shoot is unknown (the display says "??" instead). If
the  barrel is hit you can only move it in 3 degree steps, the same holds for
the  powder.  If  you  hit  the basis you can move the cannon only in a small
range.  If  a  damaged  part of the cannon is hit again, the damage goes from
light  to  heavy,  which means that the part is unuseable for the next shoot.
All damages are repaired automatically.

@endnode


@node game_menu "Game Menu"

                                @{b}2.2 Game Menu
                               ===============@{ub}

In this window you can change the settings for the games.

@{b}Gadgets@{ub}

@{" Player1-4         " link player}   Player

@{" Game Mode         " link game_mode}   Type of game
@{" # of Players      " link nr_of_players}   Number of players
@{" Game Level        " link game_level}   Difficulty of the game
@{" Weapons           " link weapons}   Weapon selection
@{" Game Mode Options " link game_mode_options}   Special settings

@{" Load Settings     " link load_settings}   Load other settings
@{" Save Settings     " link save_settings}   Save current settings
@{" Reset             " link reset}   Reset the settings
@{" Cancel            " link cancel}   Don't change the settings

@{" Start Game        " link start_game}   Use settings and start the game

@endnode


@node player "Player"

With these 4 gadgets you can change the players for the games. It is possible
to use 2, 3 or 4 players (dependent on the game-mode). To select a player you
first  have to select him from the list (Available Players) then you click on
one  of  the activated player-gadgets (e.g. Player2). You have to fill in the
selected  number  of players or the game won't start. If there are not enough
human players you can fill up the rest with computer players.

@endnode


@node game_mode "Type of game"

You can select between 4 game modes:

1) @{b}Duel Mode@{ub}:

   normal mode, 2 players

2) @{b}Tournament Mode@{ub}:

   tournament mode, 3 or 4 players (dependent on tournament mode)

3) @{b}Training Mode@{ub}:

   training mode, 2 players

4) @{b}Conquer Mode@{ub}

   conquer mode, 2 players

   The goal is to conquer the opponents castle. The distance between the two
   castles is Conquer Width*2 (represented with blazons). If a player wins a
   duel, he gets a blazon from his opponents, if he loses, he has to give it
   back. The player who first reaches the castle of the opponent has won.

For more options see @{" Game Mode Options " link game_mode_options}!

@endnode


@node nr_of_players "Number of players"

With this gadget you can select the number of players for the tournament-mode
"Each vs Each".

@endnode


@node game_level "Difficulty of the game"

You can select between 3 difficulty levels: @{b}Easy@{ub}, @{b}Medium@{ub} and @{b}Hard@{ub}.

The only difference for now is the maximum strength and the maximum change of
the wind speed. This can change in the future.

@endnode


@node weapons "Weapon selection"

You  can  select  between  two  modes:  "Original" and "Enhanced". "Original"
corresponds  to  the game principle of all previous BattleDuel versions, i.e.
there  is  only  one weapon (the normal cannonball). "Enhanded" gives you the
possibility to use all of the new weapons.

@endnode


@node load_settings "Load other settings"

A  settings  file (with players, game mode, game mode options, ...) is loaded
from  the  settings  directory.  The  file  'Default.set' is loaded everytime
BattleDuel  is started. If you want to save the current settings as "default"
you must use this name!

@endnode


@node save_settings "Save current settings"

A settings file (with players, game mode, game mode options, ...) is saved to
the  settings  directory. You don't have to enter the extension ".set"; it is
appended automatically.

@endnode


@node reset "Reset the settings"

The settings for players, game mode and number of players is reset to default
values.

@endnode


@node cancel "Don't change the settings"

The new settings are @{b}not@{ub} used and the window is closed.

@endnode


@node start_game "Use settings and start the game"

The settings are used and the game is started.

@endnode


@node game_mode_options "Special settings"

                            @{b}2.3 Game Mode Options
                           =======================@{ub}

In  this  window  you  can change the settings for the current game mode (all
other settings are not changeable!).

@{b}Duel Options@{ub}

@{" Best of x Duels      " link best_of_x_duels }   How many duels?
@{" Unlimited # of Duels " link unlimited_nr_of_duels}   Unlimited number of duels?
@{" Who starts           " link who_starts}   Which player starts the next duel?

@{b}Training Options@{ub}

@{" Wind                 " link wind}   Wind?
@{" Max Wind             " link max_wind}   Maximum wind speed
@{" Max Change           " link max_change}   Maximum change of the wind speed
@{" Show Flight Path     " link show_flight_path}   Show the flight path?

@{b}Tourmament Options@{ub}

@{" Mode                 " link mode}   Tournament mode

@{b}Conquer Options@{ub}

@{" Conquer Width        " link conquer_width}   Distance between castles

@{b}Misc Options@{ub}

@{" Dynamic Wind         " link dynamic_wind}   Dynamic wind?
@{" Wind Change          " link wind_change}   Maximum wind change
@{" Cannon Fail          " link cannon_fail}   Failure of cannon possible?
@{" Probability          " link probability}   Probability for cannon failure
@{" No Full Hits         " link no_full_hits}   No full hits possible?

@{" Use                  " link use}   Use current settings
@{" Cancel               " link cancel}   Don't change the settings

@endnode


@node best_of_x_duels "How many duels?"

Here  you  can enter the maximum number of duels. This value is only an upper
bound, you certainly can quit the game earlier. The allowed range is 1..99.

@endnode


@node unlimited_nr_of_duels "Unlimited number of duels?"

If  you  don't  know  how  many  duels you want to play, simply activate this
gadget. You then really can play an unlimited number of duels, but you should
quit the game after 10 hours :-)

@endnode


@node who_starts "Which player starts the next duel?"

With  this  gadget  you  can  select  if  the loser, the winner or a random
player  starts the next duel (for the first duel a randomly selected player
is used).

@endnode


@node wind "Wind?"

With this gagdet you can select between wind and no wind.

@endnode


@node max_wind "Maximum wind"

Here you can enter the maximum wind speed. The allowed range is 1..20.

@endnode


@node max_change "Maximum change of the wind"

Here you can enter the maximum change of the wind strength. The allowed range
is 1..10.

@endnode


@node show_flight_path "Show the flight path?"

The  flight  path  of  the cannonball with the current settings is shown (and
erased).  This option is particularly useful for beginners to learn the game.
(If your computer is slow you won't have much fun with this option, because a
lot of calculation is necessary!)

@endnode


@node mode "Tournament mode"

@{b}K.O. System@{ub}

Only  the  winner  of  a  duel  advances one round (there are 3 duels: 2 half
finals and one final). This mode is only possible with 4 players!

@{b}Each vs Each@{ub}

Each  player  has to play against each other, i.e. with 3 players there are 3
duels  and  with  4 player there are 6. The player with the most victories is
the winner.

@endnode


@node conquer_width "Distance between castles"

Here you can change the distance between the two castles. The distance is
always doubled, i.e. 3 means 6 fields and 5 means 10 fields.

@endnode


@node dynamic_wind "Dynamic Wind"

Dynamic wind means that the wind changes while the cannonball is flying. This
causes the flight path to be less predictable.

@endnode


@node wind_change "Maximum wind change"

With  this  gadget you can select the maximum change of the dynamic wind. The
allowed range is 1 to 30.

@endnode


@node cannon_fail "Fail of cannon possible?"

With  this  gadget you can select, wether you want to have cannon failures or
not.  A  cannon  failures always happens at random. If your cannon fails, the
cannonball  has  not  as  much power as normally. It is possible that you hit
yourself if the wind is strong enough :-)

@endnode


@node probability "Probability for cannon fail"

You  can  select  the  probability for a cannon failure. The allowed range is
1..20%.

@endnode


@node no_full_hits "No full hits possible?"

If  you  activate  this  gadget  then  full  hits  (i.e. 100%) are not longer
possible. The maximum damage per hit now is 75%.

@endnode


@node use "Use current settings"

The settings are used and the window is closed.

@endnode


@node cancel "Don't change the settings"

The settings are @{b}not@{ub} used and the window is closed.

@endnode


@node player_menu "Player Menu"

                               @{b}2.4 Player Menu
                              =================@{ub}

Within  this  window  you  can enter new players, remove old ones, change the
skill level for computer players and change the player names. Furthermore you
can view the actual statistics for every player.

@{b}Active Players@{ub}

In this list all players are shown. It contains the following columns:

   Typ         : @{b}C@{ub} for computer, @{b}H@{ub} for human players
   Location    : @{b}L@{ub} for local players, @{b}N@{ub} for network players
   Skill Level : @{b}E@{ub} for Easy, @{b}M@{ub} for Medium, @{b}H@{ub} for Hard
                 @{b}-@{ub} for human players
   Name        : Name of player
   
@{b}Player statistics@{ub}

   Duels          : Number of duels
   Victories      : Number of victories
   Total Shots    : Number of shots
   Total Hits     : Number of hits
   Total Hit %    : Percentage (Number of hits per 100 shots)
   Skill Level    : Skill level (only for computer players)
   Score          : Total of all scores
   Average Score  : Average of all scores
   Hit % Analysis : Figure of the Hit % of the last 50 duels:
                    the higher the value, the better
                    the red line shows the mean value (corresponds to Total
                    Hit %)
   Rank           : Actual rank

@{b}Gadgets@{ub}

@{"Add          " link add_player}   Enter new player
@{"Remove       " link remove_player}   Remove player
@{"Edit         " link edit_player}   Change values of player

@{"Reset Values " link reset_values}   Reset the player statistics

@endnode


@node add_player "Enter new player"

You  can enter the name, the type and the skill level of a player. Every name
can appear only once. If you enter a name that already is present you have to
enter a different one. In the most cases you will select 'Human' for the type
of  a player, because the computer players are only the opponents and can not
be played by humans. The skill level is only for computer players. The higher
it is, the better the computer will play.

@endnode


@node remove_player "Remove player"

You  have to select the player you want to remove from the player list. After
a security request it is deleted and gone forever.

@endnode


@node edit_player "Change values of player"

You can change the name of a human player afterwards. In addition to this you
can  change  the  skill  level  of  computer  players.  For  the  values  see
@{"Enter new player" link add_player}.

@endnode


@node reset_values "Reset the player statistics"

After a security request all values of the player statistics are reset to 0.

@endnode


